Dual Clearing | Investment Products | Insurance Services | Women Advisors




Dual Clearing
SagePoint is committed to supporting our advisors in the way they are most comfortable rather than making them conform to our preferences. To that end we offer dual clearing arrangements through both Pershing and National Financial Services. Our goal is to make any transition as seamless as possible to both our advisors and the clients they serve.
Pershing
Pershing has been a leading global provider of financial business solutions for 75 years, and serves many of the world’s most respected financial organizations. In addition to SIPC protection, accounts held at Pershing have coverage in excess of SIPC limits through Lloyd’s of London. Pershing’s parent company, the Bank of New York Mellon, has $27.6 trillion in assets under custody or administration and $1.6 trillion under management.*
Our relationship with Pershing offers you access to NetX360, Pershing’s revolutionary technology platform providing the tools needed to manage clients’ accounts, deliver first-rate service, and develop new sales and revenue opportunities. NetX360 offers one complete solution to efficiently manage your entire business, whether commission or fee-based.
National Financial Services (NFS)
National Financial Services is a leading provider of clearing and custody solutions to more than 300 broker-dealers throughout the United States. Established in 1983, NFS, a Fidelity Investments company, is one of the largest providers of brokerage services with more than 25 million brokerage accounts representing $3.2 trillion in assets. Its parent company, Fidelity Investments is one of the world’s largest providers of financial services, with custodial assets of $4.6 trillion, including managed assets of $1.9 trillion.*
The strength and reputation associated with Fidelity Investments is one of the many reasons SagePoint is pleased to partner with NFS. Our relationship with NFS provides trade execution, clearing, and other related services for your commission and fee-based brokerage accounts and offers access to a dedicated service model, leading investment solutions, and access to Streetscape—a powerful global trading platform.
Pershing, NFS and their affiliates are not affiliated with SagePoint Financial or Advisor Group.
* Dates as of (12-31-14)



SagePoint is committed to making sure we support our advisors in the ways they are most comfortable rather than making them conform to our preferences.
Ready to Talk?



Investment Products
SagePoint advisors have the flexibility to access financial products from hundreds of companies. This level of independence enables you to provide truly sound advice to your clients with the confidence that you’re presenting among the best available solutions for their needs.
It is also important to state that SagePoint respects your status as an independent financial advisor and will never exert any pressure to sell proprietary products. You are encouraged always to determine the best solutions for and with your clients to meet their specific financial needs.
Our Internal Sales Team will also consult with you one-on-one to offer recommendations and support, while providing strategic insight, positioning and comparisons among the extensive range of products we enable you to offer.
Mutual Funds
Mutual funds are often the financial cornerstone for a vast number of Americans who have worked hard throughout their lives and want access to investments designed to meet their evolving needs throughout their lifetimes. For this reason, SagePoint offers a substantial list of funds designed for every need.
Learn about mutual funds options
Variable Annuities
For the right client in the appropriate stage of life, variable annuities can be an attractive option. Through SagePoint, you have access to a wide range of variable annuities that are designed to provide solutions for lifetime income. We also provide an Annuity Intelligence tool that can help you compare and contrast the best annuities in the market
