Insurance Services
The Insurance Services department functions as the insurance product marketing support department for SagePoint. Their job is to work with you to help you make the best decisions regarding insurance products and insurance based solutions. We start by understanding what role insurance plays in your practice, and what type of service you need to grow that segment of your practice, and then deliver that support per your needs.
Expanded Choice
We have designated several insurance companies as Focus Life carriers and certain Brokerage General Agencies (BGAs) as preferred distributors. Doing business with these organizations gives you a wide range of options while allowing you to place your business through SagePoint. Of course, open architecture model also allows you a variety of ways to place your insurance business.
The Focus Life carriers are specially selected insurance carriers who share our vision of maintaining a pro-active, aggressive internal insurance department and have demonstrated their willingness and ability to not only assist us in delivering value to you but to also facilitate the access and distribution of competitive, quality products and services. Each Focus Life Carrier has agreed to provide underwriting, advanced planning, and operations support. Many will also provide you with point-of-sale support on more challenging cases. Click link below to access a complete list of Focus Life and BGA carriers.
Advisor Insurance Solutions Center (AISC)
Our internal BGS provides multi-carrier opportunities and singular support for our advisors. The services include:

Priority Processing of New Business
Objective, Dedicated Service From Quote to Policy Execution
Comprehensive Case Management
External Sales Support

And, AISC’s Electronic Multi-Carrier Submissions system lets you place term business directly through Advisor Portal!
Point of Sale Support
SagePoint leverages a team of experienced Regional Life Specialists, who are ready to assist advisors in evaluating their clients’ life insurance needs. These specialists help identify clients with life insurance needs, explain strategies, and help grow an advisor’s life insurance business. As a value-added resource, specialists will be involved as much or as little as you deem appropriate.
VIP Program
Our top insurance advisors are included in our VIP Program as either Premier or Select members. Benefits of membership include exclusive access to advanced insurance education and training.
Vive On-Line Term Insurance
Vive (formerly, tioTERM) provides instant, reliable, term quotes based on a few simple health questions that every client can answer. Not just an order submission process or a quote engine, Vive is everything you need to quote, compare, select, and order a term life policy, all on-line in an intuitive, easy-to-use, website. Competing products are quoted side-by-side for easy comparison, and product details are available online at the touch of a button. Orders are submitted through a simplified online form so users never contend with burdensome applications or amendments or waste valuable time scheduling exams or ordering medical records. Click link below to access a list of Vive carriers.
Term Intelligence
Access our Electronic Multi-Carrier Submissions system directly through the Advisor Portal to manage term life business efficiently.
